  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Balakleya Fire Shelter Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	ADRA will be responding with conditional cash transfers to 37 HHs to assist with basic home repairs to damage created from the explosion and fires.
&#x2022;	The assistance is planned in a form of unconditional cash for light shelter repair and basic survival needs. Most vulnerable HHs, which receive no state support, will use it for repair or for buying the furniture and other things, damaged by fire and shatters.
&#x2022;	Independently from family size, the HH will receive 300 USD for light repair in this project.  This sum will be transferred all at once to bank accounts of members of affected families
&#x2022;	Cash is considered the relevant assistance as local market system was not destroyed and affected population can spend finances to rebuild the dwelling or to more urgent needs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	March 23, 2017 at 2.46 AM (0046 GMT) unknown saboteurs blew up a warehouse storing tank ammunition at a military base in the city of Balakleya (about 100 kilometers from the frontline of Ukraine&#x2019;s war against Russian-backed separatists). 
&#x2022;	The massive fire prompted the evacuation of about 20,000 people.
&#x2022;	243 buildings were damaged, including 87 private homes</narrative>
  </description>
